## CarSpotter landing — environment variables
## Copy this file to `.env.local` for dev, or set these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
## The app falls back gracefully when keys are missing:
##  - no ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  → /api/identify returns a random mock car
##  - no STRIPE_*           → /api/checkout returns 503 and the FE falls back to mailto
##  - no KV_*               → user state lives in module memory (lost on cold start)

# ── Claude API (for real car identification via vision) ─────────────────────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ── Stripe (for real paid checkout) ─────────────────────────────────────────
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...

# Create products + prices in Stripe dashboard, then paste their `price_...` IDs:
STRIPE_PRICE_SPOTTER_MONTHLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_SPOTTER_YEARLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_COLLECTOR_MONTHLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_COLLECTOR_YEARLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_CONCOURS_MONTHLY=price_...
STRIPE_PRICE_CONCOURS_YEARLY=price_...

# ── Vercel KV / Upstash Redis (for persistent user + scan state) ────────────
# Create in Vercel → Storage → KV. These get injected automatically when linked.
KV_REST_API_URL=https://...
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=...
